should contact him directly. - Mod.MHJ]

[If only 86 000 cattle were vaccinated in 2009 (para.2), one wonders
what they did with the rest of the 11 million doses of vaccine they
produced? Same question re the 2008 production of 18 630 250 doses,
when only 132 610 head were vaccinated -- see 2009 archive below.
Vaccine shelf life, as far as I can determine, is about 3 years. -
Mod.JW]

